Programming Assignment 7

Short Description:
This program makes use of a Dictionary ADT created in C++ to perform quick look ups through the use of a Binary Search Tree.

Build:
A Makefile is provided and can be used to build the program. This can be accomplished within the directory where the program files are located by typing 'make Order'. 

Running:
The format for running Order <input file> <output file>

Cleaning:
To remove all files that were generated by the compiler, type the command 'make clean’.

FILES-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Order.cpp:
Program used to read in and output results of the dictionary

Dictionary.cpp:
Source file containing the implementation of the Dictionary ADT

Dictionary.h:
Header file containing function prototypes for the Dictionary ADT

DictionaryTest.cpp:
File containing thorough testing of the Dictionary ADT

Makefile:
File that creates an executable binary file called Order 

README:
File displaying contents of PA7 and any other messages for graders
